Your Important Dates

These are all of the projected release dates that the Time Computation Unit has calculated for your sentence. These dates may change if you receive a disciplinary infraction and lose release credits, or if your release credits are restored. You may also see some dates appear or disappear depending on if you meet the qualifying criteria. Tap the “Learn more about …” button under any of the dates below to learn more about that release date and its criteria.

Standard Transition Program (STP)
5 días from today
2 de noviembre de 2025

Your date is coming up soon! Remaining compliant with the criteria is the best way to keep your date from changing.

Learn more about STP
Community Supervision Begin Date (CSBD)
31 de enero de 2026Only eligible if you meet the criteria
(3 meses and 3 días from today)

A discretionary release up to 90 days before your ERCD. You must meet the criteria listed in ADCRR Department Order 1002. You may also hear this called a “Temporary Release” (TR) date.

Learn more about CSBD
Earned Release Credit Date (ERCD)
18 de abril de 2026
(5 meses and 21 días from today)

The earliest date you can be released based on Earned Release Credits.

Learn more about ERCD
Sentence Expiration Date (SED, “100%”, “Flat Time”)
29 de julio de 2026
(9 meses and 1 día from today)

The full term of your prison sentence (often called “100%” or “Flat Time”). You will be released on this date if you are not eligible for earlier release types. If you have to complete Community Supervision after your prison term, you must still agree to certain conditions of supervision.

Learn more about SED
Community Supervision End Date (CSED)
28 de septiembre de 2026
(11 meses from today)

The last day that you can be under ADCRR supervision for your current sentence.

Learn more about CSED
